result.name: Roast Goose King - Sham Shui Po

reviews.text: It's standard diner. Only goose/duck value (still fat). Roast pork is just ok. Boiled or steam chicken is too much fat

Got my 烧鹅 (roast goose) fix here in Hong Kong after more than 7 years absence! Juicy but fatty, though easy to pick off the fats.  Have always been amazed at the rates prices of food inflates in Hong Kong.  HKG 81 for a plate of rice + HKG 9 for a bowl of soup!
Loved their food
